<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 17 at 9:16PM CDT  by NWS Shreveport</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of western Union,
southeastern Columbia Counties in southwestern Arkansas and north
central Claiborne Parishes through 1000 PM CDT...
At 915 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Atlanta, or 13 miles north of Homer, moving northeast at 60 mph.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
El Dorado, Smackover, Norphlet, Haynesville, Calion, Lisbon, Atlanta,
Wesson, Hew Hope, Newell, Marysville, Cairo, Three Creeks and Kenova.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
